node.text:
We finally got round to starting our next wee project ❤  ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Right next to our house we have the @gmundner.keramik factory and today we were visited by Beate and Roland who work there and are going to be helping us making our bowls that we will be raffling off for charity come the end of september. (Date not official)
  ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
We are planning on making 5 bowls again with Nalas paw print in the centre, the factory is quite loud so they wanted to bring the workshop to our house so Nala wouldnt get spooked by the loud noises. After mixing the plaster it was Nalas turn to work her magic and leave her best pawprints in the mould 🐾❤
  ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Really looking forward to see how they turn out 😍

node.text:
Our donation today is going to @nowzadrescue in Afghanistan who are in desperate need of help. 🇦🇫
They are an animal charity set up by ex Royal Marine called Pen Farthing and they look after cats, dogs and other animals. They are trying to raise £200k to charter a cargo plane to get their animals and vets out of Afghanistan.
For more information on how to donate visit their facebook site Nowzad. 👈❤

Hows everyone doing out there? 😊
  ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Some good news, money from the 2021 calendar has finally been counted and we managed to raise £90830!!!
Massive thank you to everyone who bought a calendar, because of this we are able to help many more animals ❤
  ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Our first donation from this money pool goes towards @edensanctuary who are desperately trying to raise funds to move their animals to a new home as their landlord evicted them from their current place. To find out more about their story or if you would like to send them a donation check them out @edensanctuary 👈❤
